sec.p:
In this section we mentioned various surveys that have been performed and are related to IEMS. In Table 2 we present a comparison between these surveys and our work. In the next sections, we will show that each IEMS, regardless of its type, follows a similar architecture. Our work breaks down their components and studies state-of-the-art designs, devices and algorithmic approaches. These IEMS implementations are based on requirements extracted from our need to tackle the factors that cause energy overconsumption. To the best of our knowledge, until now, no survey has been performed that both discusses approaches towards energy efficiency, factors that affect it and at the same time present a overview of the architecture, the components and their categories. Moreover, our work presents a novel classification on IEMS based on the type of actuation they incorporate and discusses major open problems of these classes and suggests research directions that will help community to develop better and more efficient IEMS, specialized for each specific installation environment.Table 1
